dd soaked cherries and angelica and Kirsch then stir. Clean mixing bowl."},{"content":" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Place chilled cream and lightly whip on <b>speed 3<b> to soft peak stage, watching carefully to avoid over-whipping."},{"content":"Place rice mixture over a bowl of iced water and stir until it slightly thickens due to the gelatine (see tip). Fold in whipped cream. Pour into chilled dariole moulds and refrigerate until fully set."},{"content":"To demould puddings, dip moulds in warm water for 7-10 seconds then invert onto the centre of a dessert plate. Serve, or decorate with fresh berries and raspberry sauce."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Make this recipe in metal moulds so the puddings are easier to demould.","A good sign of a mixture thickening is that it leaves a trail that holds it's shape momentarily when you drizzle it back into the bowl from a spoon."],"basicInfo":["easy","40m","2h","6 portions"]}